Setting Theme for Figures

theme <- 
  theme_bw() + theme(axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                     panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
                     panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
                     panel.background = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_text(margin=margin(0,6,0,0))) + #space between xaxis and title
  theme(axis.title.x=element_text(margin=margin(8,0,0,0))) + #space between xaxis and title
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(color = "black", size = 12)) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_text(color = "black", size = 14)) +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(color = "black", size = 12)) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_text(color = "black", size = 14)) +
  theme(legend.text= element_text(color = "black", size = 12)) +
  theme(legend.title= element_text(color = "black", size = 14)) +
  theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(color = "black", size = 14)) + 
  theme(plot.margin=unit(c(0.2,0.2,0.2,0.2),"cm")) + 
  theme(legend.key.height=unit(0.4, "cm")) + 
  theme(legend.key.width=unit(0.2, "cm")) + 
  theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size = 14)) + #this will only be used if we create a facet plot at some point 
  theme(strip.background = element_blank())

PTern_Grow = read.csv("PMITern_2021Growth_Raw.csv", header = TRUE)
PTern_Dates = read.csv("PMITern_2021Dates_Raw.csv", header = TRUE)

#tidying the growth data 
PTern_GrowthData =
PTern_Grow %>%
  gather(Date, Mass, c(10:63)) %>%
  separate(Mass, c("Mass", "Wing")) %>%
  mutate(Number = Date) %>%
  select(-Date) %>%
  left_join(PTern_Dates, by = "Number") %>%
  select(Species, Island, Band, Nest, Band, Final_Status, Hatch_Date, Date, Mass, Wing, Chick) %>%
  mutate(Chick_Age_Days = as.numeric(mdy(Date) - mdy(Hatch_Date)), Mass = as.numeric(Mass), Wing = as.numeric(Wing), Hatch_Date = mdy(Hatch_Date)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Mass))
## Warning: Expected 2 pieces. Additional pieces discarded in 2 rows [2196, 5605].

#tidying mass asymptote 
Asymptote =
  PTern_GrowthData %>%
  group_by(Species, Island, Band, Final_Status, Hatch_Date, Chick) %>%
  filter(Chick_Age_Days > 15 & Chick_Age_Days < 28) %>%
  summarize(mass_asymptote = mean(Mass, na.rm = TRUE), wing_asymptote = mean(Wing, na.rm = TRUE))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Species', 'Island', 'Band',
## 'Final_Status', 'Hatch_Date'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
#linear growth mass
LinearGrowth_mass =
PTern_GrowthData %>%
  filter(Chick_Age_Days > 2 & Chick_Age_Days < 14) %>%
  group_by(Species, Island, Band, Final_Status, Hatch_Date, Chick) %>%
  do(tidy(lm(Mass ~ Chick_Age_Days, data = .))) %>%
  filter(term == "Chick_Age_Days") %>%
  mutate(slope_mass = estimate, Band = as.character(Band)) %>%
  select(Species, Island, Band, slope_mass, Final_Status, Hatch_Date, Chick) %>%
  ungroup()

#linear growth wing 

LinearGrowth_wing =
PTern_GrowthData %>%
  filter(Chick_Age_Days > 2 & Chick_Age_Days < 14) %>%
  group_by(Species, Island, Band, Final_Status, Hatch_Date, Chick) %>%
  do(tidy(lm(Wing ~ Chick_Age_Days, data = .))) %>%
  filter(term == "Chick_Age_Days") %>%
  mutate(slope_wing = estimate, Band = as.character(Band)) %>%
  select(Species, Island, Band, slope_wing, Final_Status, Hatch_Date, Chick) %>%
  ungroup()

#good to specify what you are joining by 
join_1= 
  LinearGrowth_mass %>%
  full_join (LinearGrowth_wing) 
## Joining with `by = join_by(Species, Island, Band, Final_Status, Hatch_Date,

mass_wing_2021= 
  join_1 %>%

## Joining with `by = join_by(Species, Island, Band, Final_Status, Hatch_Date,

survival_plot_2017<-
mass_wing_2017  %>%
  group_by(Species) %>% 
  mutate(Fate = ifelse(Fate == "DEAD","DIED","FLEDGED")) %>%

MassAsymp_null =
PMI_all %>%
  group_by(Year) %>%
  do(glance(lm(Mass_Asymp ~ 1, data = .))) %>%
  select(Year, AIC) %>% 
  rename(AIC_null = AIC)

MassAsymp_Julian=
PMI_all %>%
  group_by(Year)%>%
  do(glance(lm(Mass_Asymp ~ Julian, data = .))) %>%
  select(Year, AIC)%>%
  mutate(model = "lm_Julian")

  mutate(model = "lm_JulianMultChick")

  group_by(Year)%>%
  do(glance(lm(Mass_Asymp ~ Chick, data = .))) %>%
  select(Year, AIC)%>%
  mutate(model = "lm_Chick")

Eggshell Isotope Data

isotoperesults = read.csv("EggMembraneResults_Jamie2022.csv", header = TRUE) %>% select(Sample, delC, delN, perC, perN)

isotopereference = read.csv("EggSampleDatasheet.csv", header = TRUE) %>% select(Sample, Species, Plot, Nest, Chick, Status) %>% filter(Species %in% c("ARTE", "COTE"))

  
hatch = read.csv("PMI_2022_WingProd.csv", header = TRUE) %>%
  select(Fate, Species, Band, Plot, Nest, Chick, Hatch) %>% filter(Species %in% c("ARTE", "COTE")) 
tern_eggisotopes = 
isotoperesults %>%
  inner_join(isotopereference, by = "Sample") %>%
  left_join(hatch %>% mutate(Nest = as.character(Nest)), by = c("Species", "Plot", "Nest", "Chick")) %>%
  group_by(Sample, Species, Nest, Chick, Plot, Status, Fate, Hatch) %>%
  summarize(delC = mean(delC), delN = mean(delN)) %>%
  mutate(Sample = as.character(Sample)) %>%
  mutate(Hatch = mdy(Hatch),Julian=yday(Hatch)) %>%
  mutate(Status = ifelse(Status == "Hatched", "Hatched", "DeadEgg")) %>%
  filter(Status == "Hatched")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Sample', 'Species', 'Nest', 'Chick',
## 'Plot', 'Status', 'Fate'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
#write.csv(head(tern_eggisotopes, 30), "clipboard", row.names = FALSE)

  filter(!is.na(Hatch)) %>%
  mutate(Status = ifelse(Status == "Hatched", "Hatched", "DeadEgg")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Julian, y = delC, color = Species)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_color_manual (values= c("darkblue", "goldenrod1"))+

  geom_smooth(method = "lm")

library(SIBER)
## Warning: package 'SIBER' was built under R version 4.3.3
data_em_siber = 
  data.frame(tern_eggisotopes %>%
  mutate(iso1 = delC, iso2 = delN) %>%
  mutate(community = 1, group = Species) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  select(iso1, iso2, group, community))

siber.em <- createSiberObject(data_em_siber)
siber.em$sample.sizes
##   ARTE COTE
## 1   13    9
# Calculate summary statistics for each group: TA, SEA and SEAc
em.ML <- groupMetricsML(siber.em)
print(em.ML) #isotope niche and convex hull area for the two species
##         1.ARTE    1.COTE
## TA   0.8150000 0.8600000
## SEA  0.3534553 0.5689787
## SEAc 0.3855876 0.6502613
#options for running jags
  parms <- list()
  parms$n.iter <- 2 * 10^4    #number of iterations to run the model for
  parms$n.burnin <- 1 * 10^3  #discard the first set of values
  parms$n.thin <- 10      #thin the posterior by this many
  parms$n.chains <- 2        # run this many chains

#define the priors
  priors <- list()
  priors$R <- 1 * diag(2)
  priors$k <- 2
  priors$tau.mu <- 1.0E-3

  #  fit the ellipses which uses an Inverse Wishart prior
  #  on the covariance matrix Sigma, and a vague normal prior on the
  #  means. Fitting is via the JAGS method.
  ellipses.posterior <- siberMVN(siber.em, parms, priors)

   # The posterior estimates of the ellipses for each group can be used to
   # calculate the SEA.B for each group.
  SEA.B <- siberEllipses(ellipses.posterior)

  siberDensityPlot(SEA.B, xticklabels = colnames(em.ML),
                  xlab = c("Community | Group"),
                  ylab = expression("Standard Ellipse Area " ('permille' ^2) ),
                  bty = "L",
                  las = 1,
                  main = "SIBER ellipses on each group",
                  ylim = c(0,1.5)
                  )

# red x's for the ML estimated SEA-c
  points(1:ncol(SEA.B), em.ML[3,], col="red", pch = "x", lwd = 2)

  # Calculate some credible intervals
  cr.p <- c(0.95, 0.99) # vector of quantiles

   #call to hdrcde:hdr using lapply()
  SEA.B.credibles <- lapply(
    as.data.frame(SEA.B),
    function(x,...){tmp<-hdrcde::hdr(x)$hdr},
    prob = cr.p)

  SEAB_estimates = data.frame(SEA.B)
